Name: django-taggit
Version: 0.2.0
Summary: django-taggit is a reusable Django application for simple tagging.
Home-page: http://github.com/alex/django-taggit/tree/master
Author: Alex Gaynor
Author-email: alex.gaynor@gmail.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: django-taggit
        =============
        
        ``django-taggit`` a simpler approach to tagging with Django.  Add it to your
        ``INSTALLED_APPS` then just add a TaggableManager to your model and go:
        
        from django.db import models
        
        from taggit.managers import TaggableManager
        
        class Food(models.Model):
        # ... fields here
        
        tags = TaggableManager()
        
        
        Then you can use the API like so:
        
        >>> apple = Food.objects.create(name="apple")
        >>> apple.tags.add("red", "green", "delicious")
        >>> apple.tags.all()
        [<Tag: red>, <Tag: green>, <Tag: delicious>]
        >>> apple.tags.remove("green")
        [<Tag: red>, <Tag: delicious>]
        >>> Food.objects.filter(tags__in=["red"])
        [<Food: apple>, <Food: cherry>]
        
        
        Tags will show up for you automatically in forms and the admin.
        
